gamla-stan.title: Gamla stan
gamla-stan.description: Gamla stan, until 1980 officially Staden mellan broarna, is the old town of Stockholm, Sweden. Gamla stan consists primarily of the island Stadsholmen.

prins-eugens-waldemarsudde.title: Prins Eugens Waldemarsudde
prins-eugens-waldemarsudde.description:
Prince Eugen’s Waldemarsudde is one of Sweden’s most popular art 
museums, beautifully situated on Djurgården in Stockholm. The museum consists of a main building, the Mansion, built in 1903–1905 as a residence for Prince Eugen (1865–1947), and a gallery building that was added in 1913. Architect Ferdinand Boberg designed both buildings in close cooperation with Prince Eugen.

liseberg.title: Liseberg
liseberg.description: Liseberg is an amusement park located in Gothenburg, Sweden that opened in 1923. Liseberg is one of the most visited amusement parks in Scandinavia, attracting about 3 million visitors annually.

grona-lund.title: Gröna Lund
grona-lund.description: Tivoli Gröna Lund or Grönan is an amusement park in Stockholm, Sweden. It is located on the seaward side of the Djurgården island and is relatively small compared to other amusement parks, mainly due to its central location, which limits expansion.

djurgarden.title: Djurgården
djurgarden.description: Djurgården or, more officially, Kungliga Djurgården is an island in central Stockholm. Djurgården is home to historical buildings and monuments, museums, galleries, the amusement park Gröna Lund, the open air museum Skansen, the small residential area Djurgårdsstaden, yacht harbours, and extensive stretches of forest and meadows.

gothenburg-botanical-garden.title: Gothenburg Botanical Garden
gothenburg-botanical-garden.description: The Gothenburg Botanical Garden is located in Gothenburg, Sweden, and is one of the leading botanical gardens in Europe.

falu-gruva.title: Falu Gruva
falu-gruva.description: Falun Mine is a former copper mine located approximately one kilometer southwest of Falun . Mine was one of the largest mines and is since 2001 a World Heritage Site .

falu-kristine-kyrka.title: Falu Kristine Kyrka
falu-kristine-kyrka.description: Falu Kristine church is a congregation in Falu-Below Siljans contract in Västerås . The church is located in the Municipality of Falun in Dalarna County and is part of Falu parish .

folkets-park.title: Folkets Park
folkets-park.description: Folkets park, is a small park in Nørrebro in Copenhagen. Situated between Griffenfeldsgade and Stengade, build in 1971 and renovated in 2008.

foteviken-museum.title: Foteviken Museum
foteviken-museum.description: Fotevikens Museum is a museum in southern Sweden , as the first archaeological open-air museum , a Viking village represents the year 1134, which "Fotevikens Vikingareservat" is called.

furuviksparken-ab.title: Furuviksparken AB
furuviksparken-ab.description: Furuviksparken is an animal and amusement park located in Furuviksparken , about one mil east of Gävle . The zoo consists among other things of a aplandskap and among the zoo's lemurs , kangaroos , camels , turtles , fish and birds of various kinds.

ikea-museum.title: IKEA Museum
ikea-museum.description: The IKEA Museum is a museum located in Älmhult, Sweden, that opened to the public on June 30, 2016. It presents the history of the Swedish furnishing company IKEA. It replaced IKEA Through the Ages, a smaller 800 m2 exhibition that showed 20 different room settings with IKEA furniture and objects.
